LSTM – Case 1 (Positive Value)

Suppose:

Previous Long-Term Memory = 2
Forget Gate Output = 1.0 (100%)
Input Gate Output = 0.8 (80%)
Candidate Memory (tanh) = 0.9
Output Gate = 0.9
====

Stage 1 – Remember Previous Long-Term Memory (Forget Gate)

| **Item**            | **Description**                | **Calculation** | **Result**        |
| ------------------- | ------------------------------ | --------------- | ----------------- |
| Previous Cell State | Long-Term Memory               | c(t−1)          | **2**             |
| Forget Gate         | % Long-Term Memory to Remember | σ = 1.0         | **100% Remember** |
| Multiplication      | Previous Memory × Forget Gate  | 2 × 1.0         | **2**             |

Output of Stage-1 = 2

========

Stage 2 – Update New Long-Term Memory

| **Item**         | **Description**                | **Calculation** | **Result** |
| ---------------- | ------------------------------ | --------------- | ---------- |
| Input Gate       | % Potential Memory to Remember | σ = 0.8         | **80%**    |
| Candidate Memory | Generated by tanh              | tanh = 0.9      | **0.9**    |
| Multiplication   | Input Gate × Candidate Memory  | 0.8 × 0.9       | **0.72**   |
| Addition         | Stage-1 Output + New Memory    | 2 + 0.72        | **2.72**   |


New Long-Term Memory (Cell State c(t)) = 2.72

========

Stage 3 – Generate New Short-Term Memory

| **Item**     | **Description**                | **Calculation** | **Result** |
| ------------ | ------------------------------ | --------------- | ---------- |
| Cell State   | New Long-Term Memory           | c(t)            | **2.72**   |
| tanh         | Normalize Cell State           | tanh(2.72)      | **0.991**  |
| Output Gate  | % Memory to Output             | σ = 0.9         | **90%**    |
| Hidden State | Output Gate × tanh(Cell State) | 0.9 × 0.991     | **0.892**  |

New Short-Term Memory (h(t)) ≈ 0.89

=========

Complete Workflow

| **Stage**   | **Operation**                             | **Output** |
| ----------- | ----------------------------------------- | ---------- |
| **Stage 1** | Previous Memory × Forget Gate             | **2**      |
| **Stage 2** | (Input Gate × Candidate Memory) + Stage 1 | **2.72**   |
| **Stage 3** | tanh(Cell State) × Output Gate            | **0.89**   |


=======

Relation to the Slide

| **Slide Section**   | **LSTM Component**      | **Purpose**                                                                   |
| ------------------- | ----------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Stage-1**         | Forget Gate (σ)         | Decide how much of the previous long-term memory to keep.                     |
| **Stage-2 (Left)**  | Input Gate (σ)          | Decide how much new information to store.                                     |
| **Stage-2 (Right)** | Candidate Memory (tanh) | Generate new memory values.                                                   |
| **sum**             | Cell State Update (+)   | Combine retained old memory and new candidate memory.                         |
| **Stage-3 (Left)**  | Output Gate (σ)         | Decide how much memory to reveal.                                             |
| **Stage-3 (Right)** | Hidden State h(t)       | Final short-term memory used for prediction and passed to the next LSTM cell. |

